workflow.name: Transform YouTube transcripts to AI-generated GEO summaries in Notion

parameters.content:
## üé• YouTube ‚Üí GEO Summary Automation

### How it works
This workflow extracts audio from YouTube videos, transcribes the content using OpenAI Whisper, and generates structured GEO summaries (Goal-Execution-Outcome) through AI analysis. The final summary is saved to a Notion database with organized metadata, making video content searchable and actionable.

### Setup steps
1. Connect **YouTube OAuth2**, **OpenAI API**, and **Notion** credentials
2. Replace the RapidAPI key placeholder in "HTTP - Get YouTube Audio" node
3. Update the Notion database ID in the final node to match your workspace
4. Configure the Schedule Trigger interval (default: hourly)
5. Replace the hardcoded video ID with a dynamic input or playlist source
6. Test with a single video before enabling the schedule

## üì• Video Fetch & Metadata
Retrieves video details from YouTube API and prepares metadata like title, description, thumbnail, and publish date for downstream processing.

## üéß Audio Download & Transcription
Downloads audio from YouTube using RapidAPI, converts it to text via OpenAI Whisper, and filters out empty transcripts before merging with metadata.

## ü§ñ AI Analysis & GEO Extraction
Uses GPT-4o-mini with structured output parsing to analyze the transcript and generate Goal, Execution, Outcome, and Keywords in JSON format.

## üíæ Data Storage
Parses the AI-generated JSON and creates a new page in Notion with formatted GEO content and video metadata.

## üîê Credentials & Security
**Required credentials:**
- YouTube OAuth2
- OpenAI API key
- Notion API integration
- RapidAPI key (replace placeholder)

‚ö†Ô∏è Remove all personal tokens before sharing this template.

options.systemMessage:
=You are an expert YouTube content analyst AI. Your job is to analyze video content and produce structured GEO summaries that are clear, useful, and easy to rank.

Follow these rules:
- Never hallucinate
- Never invent details not present in the text
- Use only facts from the provided transcription and metadata
- Be concise, insightful, and analytical
- Do NOT repeat metadata
- Do NOT include filler text or intros
- Always output in exact JSON using the required keys

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
